Counter-Strike Source

Title- de_sonora
Author- Kirschtorte
email- EnchantingWizardOfRhythm@hotmail.com

-Description-
de_sonora is a map set in the Sonora desert, of the southwestern United states and part of Mexico. 
It was inspired by old western movies, I wanted to create a wild west/mexican feel to the map, and 
make it a practical layout, so it would be fun to play counter strike on.
I started it a long time ago, when I had a lot of free time in the summer.  There are about a 
dozen custom models that I modeled and textured myself.   I originally intended to 
do a lot more work on the map, but I started College and have had no free time for the past several
months, so I've decided to release it as is.  I also intend to release the .vmf files later on, so 
people new to mapping can learn from my map, as I won't be really finishing it to the point I'd like to

Bugs- The only major bugs I know of are some bad textures, that turn black. I neglected to replace 
them, so the'll just have to stay. Also Bots are pretty stupid on the map, but then they're stupid
on everymap, so...

files: de_sonora.bsp, and all custom models and materials used in the map. + screenshots
file size: 12,735KB
released: January/9th/2006

de_soclan - map created by redfollow3r 
special for soclan css community

Story:

Terrorists and counter-terrorists have met up for a
no-holds-barred, winner-take-all, sudden-death soccer match.
The first team to score a goal wins. Game-on!

Terrorists: Guard your goal and prevent the counter-terrorists
from scoring while trying put the ball in their goal.

Counter-terrorists: Guard your goal and prevent the terrorists
from scoring while trying put the ball in their goal.

Important information about the map:

* 32 total spawn points, 16 terrorist, 16 counter-terrorist
* As the match starts, get that ball moving with a 'nade or
  gunshot, otherwise the other team can easily line up a
  straight shot into your goal.

+ Special thanks to Benthos for all the help playtesting.
+ Thanks to everyone at Punkassfraggers.com, the best gaming
  community on the net.
+ Chevy van model by zareh.

Well, this was one of the first maps i've map that have i've seen through to the end and the end rusult I think is quite good ^^. This map is actually a remake of a map called 'snowblind' in the game '007 Nightfire' for the Ps2, XBOX and Gamecube (go buy it on eBay, its probably on a few quid =P) a fairly average first person shooter made by EA. Normally I wouldn't remake any maps but this I think needs to be put in source so more people have the chance to enjoy it seeing as how unpopular nightfire was (And rightfuly so, its local and bot multyiplayer was one of its few redeeming qualities. Anyway about the map, its a snowy map (as the title suggests =P) with one bombsite, an armoured personnel vehicle. Err.. that about all that I can say about sadley in terms of features, no dynamic HDR, custom props or textures, just good old fashioned awesome level design ^^. Works well with a small amount of players, 4 a side seems to work extreamly well ^^.

The main purpose of the map is... sniping! Can you believe it? You spawn, and there are giant 4 giant blocks around you. 3 Smaller ones, and one huge seperator between spawns. Buy a sniper (or anything else if you know how to get to the other spawns (or if you're feeling brave (or if you're pro))) and walk around the other side of the smaller blocks. TAH-DAH! A ladder! Time to climb... then snipe! If you look above you on top of the blocks, high in the sky, you will see 5 autosnipers. I'm not telling you how to get them, but rest assured, if you do, you will be in sniping heaven. The only problem is, I knew how to get there, and I still died about 5 times trying. Enjoy! :D
